ENV: Windows.
CRITICAL RULE (MUST NEVER BE FORGOTTEN): 
For EVERY shell command without exception ALWAYS prefix with: cmd /c 
Example: cmd /c ls -a ...   OR   cmd /c powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ...
ALWAYS append ; echo "===COMMAND_DONE===" at the end of the command.
Never use raw ls, dir, powershell, pwsh without cmd /c.
If any command gets stuck on Running → auto-cancel + rerun with cmd /c + echo.
This rule overrides everything. Remind yourself of this every single step.